The Garissa government has launched a programme to promote locally produced goods. The Buy Garissa, Produce, Develop your County’ initiative is meant to boost local production. Trade executive Adow Jubat yesterday said rural residents stand to benefit more. He spoke during an exhibition of locally produced soft drinks at Garissa hotel. “It will ensure the rural population gets a feel of the fruit of devolution. We shall strive to promote popular products at the subcounty levels,” he said. The only way the county could develop faster is by investing and promoting local products, Jubat said. He encouraged shops to stock local goods to benefit from tax exemptions. The county will give prioritise local products when buying goods, he said.